   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hong Kong aims to tax vehicle owners to avert total gridlock, government
officials said yesterday. Proposals released by the government for public
comment include increasing the tax on new cars to 70 per cent of the car's
total value from 40-60 per cent now, and raising annual licence fees by 40
per cent. Access to tunnels could be restricted to odd or even numbered
plates on alternate days. Quotas for new private cars and removal of tax
benefits on company cars are also being considered.
