<TEXT>
Two lawyers who operated a passport racket for Hong Kong Chinese were
yesterday jailed for three years.
Mr Paul Samrai and Mr James Walker charged up to Pounds 40,000 a time for
new passports for those wanting to leave the colony before the 1997 Chinese
takeover.
Mr Samrai had admitted conspiracy to use false documents while running the
Hong Kong end of the operation.
Mr Walker was convicted of conspiracy to use false instruments and two
charges of conspiracy to defraud.
