<HEADLINE>
FT  09 NOV 94 / World Stock Markets: Canada
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Toronto bounced back in moderate trading from five straight losing sessions.
The TSE 300 index finished 21.12 up at 4,209.09, although advances led
declines by just 359 to 357 after volume of 71.6m shares valued at CDollars
71.5m.
Eight of the 14 sub-indices gained ground, led by gold, financial services,
transportation and pipeline stocks. The heaviest losses came in real estate
and paper issues. The paper group dropped 1.68 per cent as its most heavily
weighted stock, Macmillan Bloedel, fell CDollars 7/8 to CDollars 17 3/4 in
heavy trading.
Gold shares were bid up on rising bullion prices as the New York spot price
for gold climbed USDollars 1.70 to USDollars 383.15 an ounce. The group
advanced 1.89 per cent, helped by gains for American Barrick, adding
CDollars  3/4 at CDollars 32 3/4 , and Placer Dome, up CDollars 1/2 at
CDollars 28 3/4.
