properties and operational guarantees from the discontinued Dennis Day, the
clothing manufacturer now sold.
At the operating level, profits from continuing operations were Pounds 5.13m
(Pounds 6.02m restated).
Earnings were 1.35p (losses 2.7p) per share, and the final is lifted to
0.35p (0.25p), though the total falls to 0.7p (1.35p). Shares closed down 2p
at 31p.
