<HEADLINE>
FT  09 NOV 94 / Team Lotus silent on rescuer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GRIFFITHS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Executives of Team Lotus, the grand prix racing team, arrived in Australia
yesterday for the final race of the season refusing to identify the team's
new owner, which has saved about 100 jobs at the team's headquarters in
Ketteringham, Norfolk, John Griffiths writes.
Team Lotus, which has no connection with Group Lotus, the engineering group
and maker of sports cars, had been in administration since mid-September.
The team's buyer may not be identified for several weeks but is expected to
launch a renewed attack on the world championship next year.
</TEXT>
