<HEADLINE>
FT  09 NOV 94 / Economic upturn may falter
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The recovery could be set to falter in the months ahead, if leading cyclical
indicators for October, published yesterday by the Central Statistical
Office, are to be believed.
The shorter leading index, supposed to predict turning points in the economy
about five months ahead, turned down slightly last month after rising from
May to September. The longer leading index, which is said to indicate
turning points about 13 months ahead, has been declining since July. They
have, however, proved erratic guides.
