FT  09 NOV 94 / European works council formed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD DONKIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
United Biscuits yesterday became the first British company to establish a
works council, Richard Donkin writes.
The voluntary agreement with UK and European unions is the first of what are
expected to be a number of such agreements involving UK multinational
companies in spite of the British government's opt-out from the European
Works Council directive.
United Biscuits said yesterday that the works council made sound business
sense.
It said that leaving out its British employees, which it would be entitled
to do under the opt-out conditions, would be 'counter-productive'.
